snippet.textDisplay: This song gives me goose bumps. My uncle (mothers elder brother) was martyred in 1971 (Sitara e Bisalat) he was a GD pilot, 26 years old. My father fought in 65 and 71, was taken a POW in 1971. Shabeer Sharif was his course mate, close friend and from his regiment, 6FF. When I listen to this song, I feel as if Im living all those moments of glory, heroism and unwavering loyalty displayed by those men who valiantly fought and gave their lives for our homeland.
snippet.textOriginal: This song gives me goose bumps. My uncle (mothers elder brother) was martyred in 1971 (Sitara e Bisalat) he was a GD pilot, 26 years old. My father fought in 65 and 71, was taken a POW in 1971. Shabeer Sharif was his course mate, close friend and from his regiment, 6FF. When I listen to this song, I feel as if Im living all those moments of glory, heroism and unwavering loyalty displayed by those men who valiantly fought and gave their lives for our homeland.
